properties.abstract: The mountains between Davos and Arosa are much less climbed than you would expect from their position close to the two well-known resorts. It is because many hikers hardly ever leave the well-developed Walser trails. Therefore, out-of-the-way mountains abound: Chüpfenflue, Mederger Flue, Tiejerflue, Amselflue. They all have in common that their west face is a sheer cliff and their east face is easily accessible. Regarding Chüpfenflue, on the way to the summit the skiing area is an uninviting landscape. Further on there is unspoilt nature. Upon reaching the picturesque Latschüel, we totally forgot that we were hiking in proximity to two busy resorts.
properties.subtitle: Pass hopping around Chüpfenflue
properties.title: From Davos to Langwies on the south ridge

segments.description: From Höhenweg, the intermediary station of Parsennbahn, take the wide trail to Strelapass. Ascend until shortly before Latschüelfurgga. Turn right towards Chüpfenflue.
segments.title: Höhenweg station - Strelapass - Latschüelfurgga

segments.description: The faint path, marked with red dots, is mostly west of the south ridge (T4+). On the unpleasant scree, walk (or scramble on the rock close to the ridge line) to the summit. Descend to Latschüelfurgga on the ascent.
segments.title: Latschüelfurgga -- Chüpfenflue south ridge and back

segments.description: From Latschüelfurgga descend the solid steps of Tritt to Chüpfer Täli. Past the small lakes at Seebjiboden descend to Langwies station via Medergen and Rongg.
segments.title: Latschüelfurgga - Medergen - Langwies

segments.description: Equally long, but with a boring last stretch on a small road, this variant is less attractive. Shortly before the lakes at Seebjiboden take a short cut to the hiking trail leading down to Sapün. A rewarding bonus of the variant is the short detour to Jatz (P. 1831) with the quaint Heimeli mountain guesthouse (Tel. 081 374 21, http://www.heimeli.ch). Continue to descend the Sapün valley to Langwies; from Dörfij on it is better to take the upper trail.
segments.title: Variant: descent to Sapün
